Nigerian youths have been called upon to take charge of their destinies by engaging policy makers in their respective constituencies. The call was made during a town hall meeting in Funtua, Katsina organised Youth Initiative for Advocacy, Growth and Advancement (YIAGA) in collaboration with Checklist foundation to educate the public on the need to youth participation in democratic governance. “As the party primary elections are drawing near, we need to do more to make sure our interest, the peoples’ interest, is represented as it should be; and this is by knowing how to hold the parties’ leadership accountable”, said comrade Abdulrahman Zubairu, of the Not Too Young To Run, Katsina state chapter. In attendance were youths from all local governments across the state